<subSubSection id="95AE1A017DECDAA6854C4D9E31EEE8AF" pageId="0" pageNumber="95" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="E025D1C0416DB1D0E8E8C71EF6A087FB" pageId="0" pageNumber="95">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="293F46EF935B00F40632CA855F3F069F" pageId="0" pageNumber="95">
Superficially, adults of 
<taxonomicName id="5894847D61D8D36651035D6D0C3214C4" authorityName="Lower" authorityYear="1901" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Syntozyga" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Syntozyga" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="232560A4140C96CCCC443F8FEE67D108" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="95">Syntozyga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are similar to many species of 
<taxonomicName id="D249ED6E7835C7987327EA02BB0D57B2" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="95" rank="tribe" tribe="Olethreutini">Olethreutini</taxonomicName>
, especially members of the subtribe Olethreutae, but they lack secondary sexual structures on the wing and legs in the male, that makes it easy to identify them from Olethreutae. In the male genitalia, 
<taxonomicName id="FF86A967BE5E7F5E9038366DB12D0F88" authorityName="Lower" authorityYear="1901" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Syntozyga" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Syntozyga" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E3B87477003E0DB5C42A160C8FDF30AF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="95">Syntozyga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is readily separated from most genera of 
<taxonomicName id="CA68972888C2DC869C8EEDE94E626F1E" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="95" rank="tribe" tribe="Olethreutini">Olethreutini</taxonomicName>
by the absence of an uncus and by strongly reduced socii. In the 
<taxonomicName id="C5F258C80B9BBA9939DB8DFE27686160" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="95" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Olethreutinae">Olethreutinae</taxonomicName>
, reduction of the appendages of the tegumen is also found in the tribe 
<taxonomicName id="B009B1942A0982869F337BAD99F3DFE5" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="95" rank="tribe" tribe="Grapholitini">Grapholitini</taxonomicName>
, but their valvae are extremely simple in structure and evenly spined. In contrast, 
<taxonomicName id="8791127DBD1EA3830387D0E2DC842912" authorityName="Lower" authorityYear="1901" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Syntozyga" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Syntozyga" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="409F3B72FA2D874814C0163D928EA180" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="95">Syntozyga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by a valva with a broad sacculus projecting distally and carrying varied vestiture such as spine clusters and strong bristles or thorns; sometimes a naked lobe (or two) is present between the cucullus and the apex of sacculus (
<taxonomicName id="35CA746BB210701E1D6ABFED27AD38B2" class="Insecta" genus="S." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="S. cerchnograpta" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cerchnograpta">
<emphasis id="502299223C4F0BEDB2B2D8C14F31B860" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="95">S. cerchnograpta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Razowski, 2014, 
<taxonomicName id="B0E49B2B6C259DFF84DDD51619716852" class="Insecta" genus="S." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="S. triangulana" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="triangulana">
<emphasis id="7825DC7E4B5DC1F587C5B000DA640750" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="95">S. triangulana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Aarvik, 2008, 
<taxonomicName id="9C828039B724D273BF2425C7F2B539E0" class="Insecta" genus="S." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="S. spirographa" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spirographa">
<emphasis id="C68832837689E6026A1CC06E2D3AB4CD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="95">S. spirographa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="9942EAD3C19D83199EDCBDDA46269F94" class="Insecta" genus="S." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="S. similispirographa" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="similispirographa">
<emphasis id="D6DE248D64A656FE5655C69A37BDE2D6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="95">S. similispirographa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov., and 
<taxonomicName id="91BBCF8B28ED9618FDC2A3B632D845EE" class="Insecta" genus="S." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="S. apicispinata" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apicispinata">
<emphasis id="44FAA949F8239F242DD18A16D644D9B4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="95">S. apicispinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov.). Detailed descriptions of the morphology of 
<taxonomicName id="8B637FE9CD3A3F927239200E3DE09647" authorityName="Lower" authorityYear="1901" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Syntozyga" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Syntozyga" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="329ECA20C5BC9D37ACFE36FAB9C6D24F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="95">Syntozyga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were provided by 
<bibRefCitation id="BCF23952A7AA9BDA880A7B623409B0C4" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5479/si.03629236.257.1" author="Diakonoff, A" journalOrPublisher="US National Museum Bulletin" pageId="0" pageNumber="95" pagination="1 - 484" refId="B6" refString="Diakonoff, A, 1968. Microlepidoptera of the Philippine Islands. US National Museum Bulletin 257: 1 - 484, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5479/si.03629236.257.1" title="Microlepidoptera of the Philippine Islands." url="https://doi.org/10.5479/si.03629236.257.1" volume="257" year="1968">Diakonoff (1968</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EA22A190703EAEB04EA0A067853C5180" author="Diakonoff, A" journalOrPublisher="Veroeffentlichungen der Zoologischen Staatssammlung Muenchen" pageId="0" pageNumber="95" refId="B8" refString="Diakonoff, A, 1973. The south Asiatic Olethreutini (Lepidoptera, Tortricidae). Zoologische Monographieen van het Rijksmuseum van Natuurlijke Historie 1, [i-xxii,] 700 pp." title="The south Asiatic Olethreutini (Lepidoptera, Tortricidae). Zoologische Monographieen van het Rijksmuseum van Natuurlijke Historie 1, [i-xxii,] 700 pp." year="1973">1973</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<bibRefCitation id="347753112A6E801291D20EA500F06A68" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1071/9780643094086" author="Horak, M" journalOrPublisher="CSIRO Publishing, Collingwood" pageId="0" pageNumber="95" refId="B15" refString="Horak, M, 2006. Monograph on Australia Lepidoptera, Vol 10: Olethreutine Moths of Australia (Lepidoptera: Tortricidae). CSIRO Publishing, Collingwood, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1071/9780643094086" title="Monograph on Australia Lepidoptera, Vol 10: Olethreutine Moths of Australia (Lepidoptera: Tortricidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1071/9780643094086" year="2006">Horak (2006)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
